==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic [[ge-]] + ''*līka-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[gelik|gelīk]], Old Saxon [[gilik|gilīk]] (Dutch [[gelijk]]), Old High German [[gilih|gilīh]] (German [[gleich]]), Old Norse [[glíkr]] ( > English [[like]]), Gothic [[𐌲𐌰𐌻𐌴𐌹𐌺𐍃]].

